Increase the number of customer locations from 11 to 15, introducing new customers with high demand (e.g., 10 units each), which is likely to exceed the combined vehicle capacity and lead to infeasibility in servicing all customers with the available vehicles.

Increase the number of vehicles from 2 to 4 while simultaneously increasing the demand of specific high-demand customers (e.g., customer indices 2, 4, and 10) by 100% to test the modelâ€™s ability to handle increased demand with additional capacity and assess the impact on total cost and feasibility.

Increase the vehicle capacity from 50 to 70 while simultaneously decreasing the demand of all customers by 50%, which is expected to test the model's ability to adapt to capacity increases and assess the impact on total cost and feasibility.
